        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> imho it's very unlikely levels will change.  Two ways to remove hell levels:</P><P>1) same way they removed the hybrid xp penalty.  Additional xp was generated each kill for the hybrids so that their climb through levels was same rate as the pure classes.  If you get a kill in 35, 40 or 45, then you'd get a small boost to speed along that level.  Long term it would shorten the climb to 60 but not by a dramatic amount.</P><P>2) the cleaner but far more intensive method would be to scrap the current xp tables, recreate a standard xp table, apply modifiers for races, and then go through every pfile and adjust current xp to the same level but on the new table.  ie, if you're 48.56% into L45, your current xp logging in after patch would be 48.56% into L45 but nowhere near same numerical xp number.</P><P>Likely #1 but I'm totally speculating</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
